Interface FutureResult<R>


  • public interface FutureResult<R>
    Result of asynchronous computation.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void cancel()
      Attempt to cancel this call.
      R get()
      This call will block until result is received or timeout occurs.
      boolean isCanceled()
      Returns true if this call was canceled before it completed normally.
      void setCallback(ResultCallback<R> resultCallback)
      Same as calling: setCallback(ResultCallback, ProgressCallback) with null as progress callback
      void setCallback(ResultCallback<R> resultCallback, ProgressCallback progressCallback)

      • isCanceled

        boolean isCanceled()

      • get

        R get()
throws java.io.IOException,

        This call will block until result is received or timeout occurs. Calling this method after calling cancel() will result into IOException.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • setCallback

        void setCallback(ResultCallback<R> resultCallback,
                 ProgressCallback progressCallback)
        Given callback interface will be invoked as result becomes available or error occurs. Calling this method after calling cancel() will result into IOException. This method will return immediately.
        Parameters:
        resultCallback - callback to be invoked when result is available or error occurs (must be non null)
        progressCallback - callback to be invoked as computation progresses, pass null for no progress feedback

      • setCallback

        void setCallback(ResultCallback<R> resultCallback)
        Same as calling: setCallback(ResultCallback, ProgressCallback) with null as progress callback
